{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan Ibn Majah","section":{"33":{"eng-name":"Etiquette","ara-name":"كتاب الأدب"}},"section_detail":{"33":{"hadithnumber_first":3657,"hadithnumber_last":3826,"arabicnumber_first":3657,"arabicnumber_last":3826}}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":3702,"arabicnumber":3702,"text":"It was narrated that Anas bin Malik said:\"O Messenger of Allah! Should we bow to one another?\" He said: \"No.\" We said: \"Should we embrace one another?\" He said: \"No, but shake hands with one another","grades":[{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Hasan"},{"name":"Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi","grade":"Hasan"},{"name":"Shuaib Al Arnaut","grade":"Daif"},{"name":"Zubair Ali Zai","grade":"Daif"}],"reference":{"book":33,"hadith":46},"chapter":{"id":15,"ara-name":"باب الْمُصَافَحَةِ","eng-name":"Shaking hands","isFirstHadith":true}}]}